## Add 
when we want to stage changes that will be included in the commit. we will use the "." to add 
all possible files. 

```sh 
git add readme.md 
git add . 
```
## Status 

Git status shows you what files will or will not be committed. 

```sh 
git status 
```
## Gitconfig file 

The git config file is what stores your local configurations for git such as 
email, name, editor and more. 

Showing the content of our git config file. 

```
git config --list
```
